I"$<p>
  I design and build websites for small businesses. I also take over upgrade and management of websites that have fallen by the wayside. I'm based near Inverness in the Scottish Highlands.
</p>

<p>In <time datetime="1999">1999</time> I created the Scottish and Celtic music specialist retail website <a href="//www.musicscotland.com/">Music Scotland</a>.
I ran this business as owner-manager from locations in Edinburgh, Stirling and the Isle of Mull.
In <time datetime="2005">2005</time> the business won the <span itemprop="award">Scots Trad Music Awards Services To Industry Award</span>.
In <time datetime="2011">2011</time> it was sold as a going concern to another Scottish music store, Oban Music.<br />
Music Scotland has sent CDs, DVDs and books to tens of thousands of customers worldwide, most of this music created by Scottish artists.</p>

<p>Since <time datetime="2011">2011</time> I’ve worked freelance, creating and/or supporting an operational web presence for a wide range of <a href="/clients">client businesses</a>.  These have included record companies and other online retailers, accommodation providers, agricultural suppliers and medical-scientific organisations.</p>

<p>Between 2017 and 2019 I was part of the Webteam at the <a href="//www.uhi.ac.uk/en/">University of the Highlands and Islands</a>, working on the University’s content management system, supporting users and developing the front end of the website.</p>

<p>I live on the rural <a href="//www.black-isle.info/">Black Isle</a>, near Inverness in the Scottish Highlands, with my wife and two children.  I own and manage Back Brae Lodge, a <a href="//mull.co">self catering holiday cottage in Tobermory</a> on the Isle of Mull.</p>

<p>In a former life I was a musician, performing internationally with <a href="//salsaceltica.com">Salsa Celtica</a> and other bands, and teaching Scottish traditional music with <a href="//feisean.org/">Feisean Nan Gaidheal</a>.</p>

<p>In an even former life, <a href="//www.ed.ac.uk/">Edinburgh University</a> gave me a degree in Biochemistry.</p>

